<subSubSection box="[199,1156,819,846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,710,846]" box="[199,1156,819,846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,819,845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1940" box="[347,465,819,845]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Spinopilar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[347,465,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Spinopilar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Latin spîna (thorn) + toponym Pilar. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926803" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4926803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926803/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" startId="3.[151,250,1865,1889]" targetBox="[157,1430,875,1835]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1865,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1865,1889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Southeastern part of Brazilian Atlantic Forest showing the distribution of the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1940" box="[1172,1279,1865,1889]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Spinopilar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1279,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Spinopilar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Colored background areas are WWF ecoregions. Magenta lines are the boundaries of Brazilian states. All species occur in type 01 biome (Tropical &amp; Subtropical Moist Broadleaf Forests) except the cave-dwelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kury &amp; Perez-Gonzalez" authorityYear="2008" box="[914,1000,1937,1961]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Spinopilar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moria">
<emphasis box="[914,1000,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">S. moria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which might be a relict from a more humid epoch. The presence of at least six yet undescribed species (white Xs) gives a glimpse of the hidden diversity of the genus. The micro-endemism in Rio de Janeiro is shown by the presence of six species in that state.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="152" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Stigmatic area fused to Cx IV along most of their area of contact (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1151,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 6" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1770,1794]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1436,181,1745]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 6A–D. Spinopilar armatus Mello-Leitão, 1940, ♂ (MNRJ 2251). A–B Cx–Fe IV &amp; stigmatic area (A ventral, B detail). C Primary trochanteral cluster, ventral. D Coxal fasciolate hyaline apophysis, apical view of bundle. CxFAp—Coxal fasciolate hyaline apophysis. PTC—primary trochanteral cluster. STC—secondary trochanteral cluster of setae. TrFAp—Trochanteral fasciolate hyaline apophysis. Scale bars: 500 μm (A); 100 μm (B); 10 μm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926815/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1161,1211,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 16" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,181,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@20.[206,1381,181,1851]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 16A–F. Spinopilar martialis spec. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ 9094) from Macaé. A Habitus, ventral. B–D Detail of stigmatic area and Cx/Tr IV (B ventral, C ventro-frontal, D right side, ventro-lateral). E Right side border of dorsal scutum at carapace, showing ozopore. F Left Cx–Tr IV, detail showing each FAp. cML—conk-shaped median lobe of stigmatic area, hSL—halter-shaped lateral lobe of stigmatic area, SC—secondary trochanteral cluster of setae, PTC—primary trochanteral cluster. Scale bars: 1 mm (C), 500 μm (A, B, D), 50 μm (E, F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926839" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926839/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">16B</figureCitation>
). Some species bear a stridulatory organ matching the ectal surface of basichelicerite and mesal surface of Pp Fe (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1328,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 17" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-27@21.[151,1436,181,1747]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 17A–E. Spinopilar martialis spec. nov., holotype ♂ (MNRJ 9094) from Macaé. A Left chelicera, ectal. B Left ba- sichelicerite, plectrum, ectal. C–E Right Fe of pedipalp (C mesal, D opposite side, detail of pars stridens, mesal, E detail of pars stridens). Scale bars: 100 μm (A, C), 50 μm (D), 20 μm (B), 10 μm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926841/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 17C–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 22" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-17@28.[151,1436,181,1807]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 22A–I. Spinopilar magistralis spec. nov., ♂ paratype (MNRJ 19189), chelicera &amp; pedipalp. A–D Left chelicerae (A frontal, B ecta, C detail of plectra, ecto-frontal, D detail of two individual plectra, ecto-frontal), E Right pedipalp, ectal, F–I Left pedipalp (F mesal, G details of Tr and Fe, meso-frontal, H Fe, detail of pars stridens, mesal, I detail of pars stridens, mesal). Scale bars: 200 μm (E, F),100 μm (A, B, G, H), 50 μm (C), 10 μm (I), 5 μm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926853/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">22B–D</figureCitation>
). Distalmost megaspine of Pp Ti much longer than the others (
<figureCitation box="[848,938,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1642,1666]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1619]" captionTargetId="figure-27@9.[151,1436,181,1619]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 7A–D. Spinopilar armatus Mello-Leitão, 1940, ♂ (MNRJ 2251). A–B Left chelicera (A mesal, B ectal). C–D Left Pedipalp (C mesal, D detail of Femur, mesal). Scale bars: 200 μm (C); 100 μm (A–B, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926817/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Cx IV of male with retroventral L-shaped apophysis with ectal branch fasciolate (
<figureCitation box="[587,725,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1710,1734]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-17@14.[151,1436,181,1687]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11A–F. Spinopilar jocheni spec. nov., ♂ paratype (MNRJ 7115) from Pedra de Guaratiba (A–B, D–F ventral, C dorsal). A Sternal region and Cx I–III. B Cx–Tr IV &amp; stigmatic area. C Cx–Tr IV &amp; surrounding region. D–F Detail of junction Cx-Tr-stigmatic area, showing lobes (colorized) (E greater magnification showing fasciolate hyaline apophyses, F detail of bundle of enlarged setae). PTC—proximal trochanteral cluster. Scale bars: 200 μm (A, B), 100 μm (C, D), 50 μm (E), 10 μm (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 11B, D</figureCitation>
). Tr IV of male with well-developed retrolateral apophysis, with secondary fasciolate branch associated with a PTC (
<figureCitation box="[730,869,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@27.[186,1402,181,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Spinopilar magistralis spec. nov., ♂ paratype (MNRJ 19189), Cx–Fe IV and stigmatic area. A Habitus, ventral, B Right Tr IV, ventral, C Ventral complex of interlocking processes, right side, fasciolate hyaline apophyses and sternites in situ, ventral, D Left Tr IV, showing primary trochanteral cluster, ventro-lateral, E Detail of PTC, F Detail of secondary trochanteral cluster of setae. STC—secondary trochanteral cluster of setae. PTC—primary trochanteral cluster. Scale bars: 500 μm (A), 100 μm (B, C, D), 20 μm (F), 10 μm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926851/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 21A–F</figureCitation>
). Malleus with a dorsobasal hyaline haematodocha (DHB, 
<figureCitation box="[234,325,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 9" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-27@11.[184,1403,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 9A–H. Spinopilar armatus Mello-Leitão, 1940 (MNRJ 2251), ♂ genitalia, distal part. A–B Lateral (A panoramic, B detail). C Dorsal. D Ventral. E Lamina parva, isolated, ventral. F–H Stylus and flabellum (F, H apical; G dorso-lateral). Macrosetae identified using colored letters A–E. DHB—dorsal hyaline button. Scale bars: 50 μm (A, C), 20 μm (B, D, F), 10 μm (E, G, H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926821/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 9C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[337,386,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 25" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,741,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-242@31.[151,1436,741,1831]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 25A–G. Spinopilar magistralis spec. nov., ♂ paratype (MNRJ 19189), distal part of genitalia (A lateral, panoramic, B detail of A, C dorsal, panoramic, D detail of C, E ventral, panoramic, F detail of E, G dorso-apical). DHB—dorsal hyaline button. Scale bars: 50 μm (A, C, E), 20 μm (B, D, F, G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926861/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">25B</figureCitation>
). Skirt with short stem, flabellum wide and short with individual barbels deeply serrate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-27@11.[184,1403,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 9A–H. Spinopilar armatus Mello-Leitão, 1940 (MNRJ 2251), ♂ genitalia, distal part. A–B Lateral (A panoramic, B detail). C Dorsal. D Ventral. E Lamina parva, isolated, ventral. F–H Stylus and flabellum (F, H apical; G dorso-lateral). Macrosetae identified using colored letters A–E. DHB—dorsal hyaline button. Scale bars: 50 μm (A, C), 20 μm (B, D, F), 10 μm (E, G, H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4926821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4926821/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="152">Figs 9E, F</figureCitation>
, 
